listedValue.definition: A relatively large natural stream of water.

listedValue.label: Reach
listedValue.definition: A straight section of a river, especially a navigable river between two bends; or an arm of the sea extending into the land.

listedValue.label: Intertidal Cay
listedValue.definition: A low, flat island of sand, coral, etc. awash or submerged at high water.

listedValue.label: Submarine Volcano
listedValue.definition: A seabed volcano, submerged at the chart sounding datum, which may or may not be active.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Category of Shoreline Construction
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Classification of shoreline construction based on use.

listedValue.label: Breakwater
listedValue.definition: A structure protecting a shore area, harbour, anchorage, or basin from waves.

listedValue.label: Groyne
listedValue.definition: A low artificial wall-like structure of durable material extending from the land to seaward for a particular purpose, such as to protect the coast or to force a current to scour a channel.

listedValue.label: Mole
listedValue.definition: A form of breakwater alongside which vessels may lie on the sheltered side only; in some cases it may lie entirely within an artificial harbour, permitting vessels to lie along both sides.

listedValue.label: Pier (Jetty)
listedValue.definition: A long, narrow structure extending into the water to afford a berthing place for vessels, to serve as a promenade, etc.

listedValue.label: Promenade Pier
listedValue.definition: A pier built only for recreational purposes.

listedValue.label: Wharf
listedValue.definition: A structure serving as a berthing place for vessels.

listedValue.label: Training Wall
listedValue.definition: A wall or bank, often submerged, built to direct or confine the flow of a river or tidal current, or to promote a scour action.

listedValue.label: Rip Rap
listedValue.definition: A layer of broken rock, cobbles, boulders, or fragments of sufficient size to resist the erosive forces of flowing water and wave action.

listedValue.label: Revetment
listedValue.definition: Facing of stone or other material, either permanent or temporary, placed along the edge of a stream, river or canal to stabilize the bank and to protect it from the erosive action of the stream.

listedValue.label: Sea Wall
listedValue.definition: An embankment or wall for protection against waves or tidal action along a shore or water front.

listedValue.label: Landing Steps
listedValue.definition: Steps at the shoreline as the connection between land and water on different levels.

listedValue.label: Ramp
listedValue.definition: (1) A sloping structure that can either be used, as a landing place, at variable water levels, for small vessels, landing ships, or a ferry boat, or for hauling a cradle carrying a vessel. (2) An accumulation of snow that forms an inclined plane between land or land ice elements and sea ice or ice shelf. Also called drift ice foot.

listedValue.label: Slipway
listedValue.definition: The prepared and usually reinforced inclined surface on which keel- and bilge-blocks are laid for supporting a vessel under construction.

listedValue.label: Fender
listedValue.definition: A protective structure designed to cushion the impact of a vessel and prevent damage.

listedValue.label: Solid Face Wharf
listedValue.definition: A wharf consisting of a solid wall of concrete, masonry, wood etc., such that the water cannot circulate freely under the wharf. The type of construction affects ship-handling; for example, a solid face wharf may give shelter from tidal streams, but under certain circumstances a cushion of water may build up between such a wharf and a ship attempting to berth at it, causing difficulties in ship handling.

listedValue.label: Open Face Wharf
listedValue.definition: A wharf supported on piles or other structures which allow free circulation of water under the wharf.

listedValue.label: Log Ramp
listedValue.definition: An inclined plane used to dump logs into the water for transport, or to haul logs out of the water for processing.

listedValue.label: Swimming Facility
listedValue.definition: An artificial pool or swimming enclosure, especially one in the open air, which may be constructed of wire mesh or heavy netting supported by cables, buoys or piles, for swimming in.

listedValue.label: Quay
listedValue.definition: A wharf approximately parallel to the shoreline and accommodating ships on one side only, the other side being attached to the shore. It is usually of solid construction, as contrasted with the open pile construction usually used for piers.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Category of Signal Station, Traffic
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Classification of station based on the traffic service provided.

listedValue.label: Port Control
listedValue.definition: A signal station for the control of vessels within a port.

listedValue.label: Port Entry and Departure
listedValue.definition: A signal station for the control of vessels entering or leaving a port.

listedValue.label: International Port Traffic
listedValue.definition: A signal station displaying International Port Traffic signals.

listedValue.label: Berthing
listedValue.definition: A signal station for the control of vessels when berthing.

listedValue.label: Dock
listedValue.definition: A signal station for the control of vessels entering or leaving a dock.

listedValue.label: Lock
listedValue.definition: A signal station for the control of vessels entering or leaving a lock.

listedValue.label: Flood Barrage Station
listedValue.definition: A signal station for the control of vessels wishing to pass through a flood control barrage.

listedValue.label: Bridge Passage
listedValue.definition: A signal station for the control of vessels wishing to pass under a bridge.

listedValue.label: Dredging
listedValue.definition: A signal station indicating when dredging is in progress.

listedValue.label: Traffic Control Light
listedValue.definition: Visual signal lights placed in a waterway to indicate to shipping the movements authorized at the time at which they are shown.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Category of Signal Station, Warning
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Classification of station based on the warning service provided.

listedValue.label: Danger
listedValue.definition: A signal or message warning of the presence of a danger to navigation.

listedValue.label: Maritime Obstruction
listedValue.definition: A signal or message warning of the presence of a maritime obstruction.

listedValue.label: Cable
listedValue.definition: A signal or message warning of the presence of a cable.

listedValue.label: Military Practice
listedValue.definition: A signal or message warning of activity in a military practice area.

listedValue.label: Distress
listedValue.definition: A station that may receive or transmit distress signals.

listedValue.label: Weather
listedValue.definition: A visual signal displayed to indicate a weather forecast.

listedValue.label: Storm
listedValue.definition: A signal or message conveying information about storm conditions.

listedValue.label: Ice Warning
listedValue.definition: A signal or message conveying information about ice conditions.

listedValue.label: Time
listedValue.definition: An accurate signal marking a specified time or time interval. It is used primarily for determining errors of timepieces. Such signals are usually sent from an observatory by radio or telegraph, but visual signals are used at some ports.

listedValue.label: Tide
listedValue.definition: A signal or message conveying information on tidal conditions in the area in question.

listedValue.label: Tidal Stream
listedValue.definition: A signal or message conveying information on condition of tidal currents in the area in question.

listedValue.label: Tide Gauge
listedValue.definition: A device for measuring the height of tide. A graduated staff in a sheltered area where visual observations can be made or it may consist of an elaborate recording instrument making a continuous graphic record of tide height against time. Such an instrument is usually actuated by a float in a pipe communicating with the sea through a small hole which filters out shorter waves.

listedValue.label: Tide Scale
listedValue.definition: A visual scale which directly shows the height of the water above chart datum or a local datum.

listedValue.label: Diving
listedValue.definition: A signal or message warning of diving activity.

listedValue.label: Water Level Gauge
listedValue.definition: A device for measuring and conveying information about the water level (non-tidal) in the area in question.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Category of Silo/Tank
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Classification based on the product for which a silo or tank is used.

listedValue.label: Silo in General
listedValue.definition: A large storage structure used for storing loose materials.

listedValue.label: Tank in General
listedValue.definition: A fixed structure for storing liquids.

listedValue.label: Grain Elevator
listedValue.definition: A storage building for grain. Usually a tall frame, metal or concrete structure with an especially compartmented interior.

listedValue.label: Water Tower
listedValue.definition: A tower supporting an elevated storage tank of water.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Category of Slope
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Classification of a stretch of ground forming a natural or artificial incline.

listedValue.label: Cutting
listedValue.definition: An excavation through high ground for a road, canal, etc.

listedValue.label: Embankment
listedValue.definition: A man-made raised long mound of earth or other material.

listedValue.label: Dune
listedValue.definition: A mound, ridge or hill of drifted material on the sea coast or in a desert.

listedValue.label: Hill
listedValue.definition: [1] A small isolated elevation, smaller than a mountain. [2] A distinct elevation generally of irregular shape, less than 1000m above the surrounding relief as measured from the deepest isobath that surrounds most of the feature.

listedValue.label: Pingo
listedValue.definition: A dome-shaped hill formed in a permafrost area when the hydrostatic pressure of freezing ground water causes the upheaval of a layer of frozen ground.

listedValue.label: Cliff
listedValue.definition: Land rising abruptly for a considerable distance above the water or surrounding land.

listedValue.label: Scree
listedValue.definition: A mass of detritus, forming a precipitous, strong slope upon a mountain-side. Also the material composing such a slope.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Category of Small Craft Facility
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Classification of services and facilities for the small craft user.

listedValue.label: Visitors Berth
listedValue.definition: A berth set aside for the use of visiting vessels.

listedValue.label: Nautical Club
listedValue.definition: A club for mariners generally associated with other small craft facilities.

listedValue.label: Boat Hoist
listedValue.definition: A hoist for lifting boats out of the water.

listedValue.label: Sailmaker
listedValue.definition: A place where sails are made or may be taken for repair.

listedValue.label: Boatyard
listedValue.definition: A place on shore where boats may be built, stored and repaired.

listedValue.label: Public Inn
listedValue.definition: A public house providing food, drink and accommodation.

listedValue.label: Restaurant
listedValue.definition: A commercial establishment serving food.

listedValue.label: Chandler
listedValue.definition: A dealer in ships' supplies.

listedValue.label: Provisions
listedValue.definition: A place where food and other such supplies are available.

listedValue.label: Doctor
listedValue.definition: A place where a doctor is available to provide medical attention.

listedValue.label: Pharmacy
listedValue.definition: A place where medical drugs are dispensed.

listedValue.label: Water Tap
listedValue.definition: A place where fresh water is available.

listedValue.label: Fuel Station
listedValue.definition: A place where fuel is available.

listedValue.label: Electricity Outlet
listedValue.definition: A place where a connection to an electrical supply is available.

listedValue.label: Bottle Gas
listedValue.definition: A place where bottled gas is available.

listedValue.label: Showers
listedValue.definition: A place where showers are available.

listedValue.label: Launderette
listedValue.definition: A place where there are facilities for washing clothes.

listedValue.label: Public Toilets
listedValue.definition: A place where toilets are available for public use.

listedValue.label: Post Box
listedValue.definition: A place where mail may be posted.

listedValue.label: Public Telephone
listedValue.definition: A place where a telephone is available for public use.

listedValue.label: Refuse Bin
listedValue.definition: A place where refuse may be dumped.

listedValue.label: Car Park
listedValue.definition: A place where cars may be parked.

listedValue.label: Parking for Boats and Trailers
listedValue.definition: A place on shore where boats and/or trailers may be parked.

listedValue.label: Caravan Site
listedValue.definition: A place where caravans may be parked or where caravan accommodation is provided.

listedValue.label: Camping Site
listedValue.definition: A place where visitors may pitch tents and camp.

listedValue.label: Sewage Pump-Out Station
listedValue.definition: A place where sewage may be pumped off a vessel.

listedValue.label: Emergency Telephone
listedValue.definition: A place where a telephone is available for emergency use only.

listedValue.label: Landing/Launching Place for Boats
listedValue.definition: A place where boats may be landed or launched.

listedValue.label: Visitors Mooring
listedValue.definition: A mooring set aside for the use of visiting vessels.

listedValue.label: Scrubbing Berth
listedValue.definition: A place where vessels may berth for the purpose of careening.

listedValue.label: Picnic Area
listedValue.definition: A place where people may go to eat a picnic.

listedValue.label: Mechanics Workshop
listedValue.definition: A place where mechanical repairs can be undertaken to engines or other vessel equipment.

listedValue.label: Guard and/or Security Service
listedValue.definition: A place where a vessel is patrolled by a security service or stored in a secure lockup.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Category of Special Purpose Mark
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Classification of an aid to navigation which signifies some special purpose.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: A mark may be a beacon, a buoy, a signpost or may take another form.

listedValue.label: Firing Danger Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark used to indicate a firing danger area, usually at sea.

listedValue.label: Target Mark
listedValue.definition: Any object toward which something is directed. The distinctive marking or instrumentation of a ground point to aid its identification on a photograph.

listedValue.label: Marker Ship Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark marking the position of a ship which is used as a target during some military exercise.

listedValue.label: Degaussing Range Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark used to indicate a degaussing range.

listedValue.label: Barge Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark of relevance to barges.

listedValue.label: Cable Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark used to indicate the position of submarine cables or the point at which they run on to the land.

listedValue.label: Spoil Ground Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark used to indicate the limit of a spoil ground.

listedValue.label: Outfall Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark used to indicate the position of an outfall or the point at which it leaves the land.

listedValue.label: ODAS
listedValue.definition: Ocean Data Acquisition System.

listedValue.label: Recording Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark used to record data for scientific purposes.

listedValue.label: Seaplane Anchorage Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark used to indicate a seaplane anchorage.

listedValue.label: Recreation Zone Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark used to indicate a recreation zone.

listedValue.label: Mooring Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating a mooring or moorings.

listedValue.label: LANBY
listedValue.definition: A large buoy designed to take the place of a lightship where construction of an offshore light station is not feasible.

listedValue.label: Leading Mark
listedValue.definition: Aids to navigation or other indicators so located as to indicate the path to be followed. Leading marks identify a leading line when they are in transit.

listedValue.label: Measured Distance Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark forming part of a transit indicating one end of a measured distance.

listedValue.label: Notice Mark
listedValue.definition: A notice board or sign indicating information to the mariner.

listedValue.label: TSS Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating a Traffic Separation Scheme.

listedValue.label: Anchoring Prohibited Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating an anchoring prohibited area.

listedValue.label: Berthing Prohibited Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating that berthing is prohibited.

listedValue.label: Overtaking Prohibited Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating that overtaking is prohibited.

listedValue.label: Two-Way Traffic Prohibited Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating a one-way route.

listedValue.label: Reduced Wake Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating that vessels must not generate excessive wake.

listedValue.label: Speed Limit Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating that a speed limit applies.

listedValue.label: Stop Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating the place where the bow of a ship must stop when traffic lights show red.

listedValue.label: General Warning Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating that special caution must be exercised in the vicinity of the mark.

listedValue.label: Sound Ship's Siren Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating that a ship should sound its siren or horn.

listedValue.label: Restricted Vertical Clearance Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating the minimum vertical space available for passage.

listedValue.label: Maximum Vessel's Draught Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating the maximum draught of vessel permitted.

listedValue.label: Restricted Horizontal Clearance Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating the minimum horizontal space available for passage.

listedValue.label: Strong Current Warning Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark warning of strong currents.

listedValue.label: Berthing Permitted Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating that berthing is allowed.

listedValue.label: Overhead Power Cable Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating an overhead power cable.

listedValue.label: Channel Edge Gradient Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating the gradient of the slope of a dredge channel edge.

listedValue.label: Telephone Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating the presence of a telephone.

listedValue.label: Ferry Crossing Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating that a ferry route crosses the ship route; often used with a 'sound ship's siren' mark.

listedValue.label: Pipeline Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark used to indicate the position of submarine pipelines or the point at which they run on to the land.

listedValue.label: Anchorage Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating an anchorage area.

listedValue.label: Clearing Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark used to indicate a clearing line.

listedValue.label: Control Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating the location at which a restriction or requirement exists.

listedValue.label: Diving Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating that diving may take place in the vicinity.

listedValue.label: Refuge Beacon
listedValue.definition: A mark providing or indicating a place of safety.

listedValue.label: Foul Ground Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating a foul ground.

listedValue.label: Yachting Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark installed for use by yachtsmen.

listedValue.label: Heliport Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating an area where helicopters may land.

listedValue.label: GNSS Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating a location at which a GNSS position has been accurately determined.

listedValue.label: Seaplane Landing Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating an area where sea-planes land.

listedValue.label: Entry Prohibited Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating that entry is prohibited.

listedValue.label: Work in Progress Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating that work (generally construction) is in progress.

listedValue.label: Mark With Unknown Purpose
listedValue.definition: A mark whose detailed characteristics are unknown.

listedValue.label: Wellhead Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating a borehole that produces or is capable of producing oil or natural gas.

listedValue.label: Channel Separation Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating the point at which a channel divides separately into two channels.

listedValue.label: Marine Farm Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating the existence of a fish, mussel, oyster or pearl farm/culture.

listedValue.label: Artificial Reef Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark indicating the existence or the extent of an artificial reef.

listedValue.label: Ice Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark, used year round, that may be submerged when ice passes through the area.

listedValue.label: Nature Reserve Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark used to define the boundary of a nature reserve.

listedValue.label: Fish Aggregating Device
listedValue.definition: A fish aggregating (or aggregation) device (FAD) is a man-made object used to attract ocean going pelagic fish such as marlin, tuna and mahi-mahi (dolphin fish). They usually consist of buoys or floats tethered to the ocean floor with concrete blocks.

listedValue.label: Wreck Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a wreck.

listedValue.label: Customs Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a customs checkpoint.

listedValue.label: Causeway Mark
listedValue.definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a causeway.

listedValue.label: Wave Recorder
listedValue.definition: A surface following buoy used to measure wave activity.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Category of Temporal Variation
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: An assessment of the likelihood of change over time.

listedValue.label: Extreme Event
listedValue.definition: Indication of the possible impact of a significant event (for example hurricane, earthquake, volcanic eruption, landslide, etc), which is considered likely to have changed the seafloor or landscape significantly.

listedValue.label: Likely to Change and Significant Shoaling Expected
listedValue.definition: Continuous or frequent change (for example river siltation, sand waves, seasonal storms, ice bergs, etc) that is likely to result in new significant shoaling.

listedValue.label: Likely to Change But Significant Shoaling Not Expected
listedValue.definition: Continuous or frequent change (for example sand wave shift, seasonal storms, ice bergs, etc) that is not likely to result in new significant shoaling.

listedValue.label: Likely to Change
listedValue.definition: Continuous or frequent change to non-bathymetric features (for example river siltation, glacier creep/recession, sand dunes, buoys, marine farms, etc).

listedValue.label: Unlikely to Change
listedValue.definition: Significant change to the seafloor is not expected.

listedValue.label: Unassessed
listedValue.definition: Not having been assessed.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Category of Tidal Stream
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Classification of the alternating horizontal movement of water associated with the rise and fall of the tide caused by tide producing forces.

listedValue.label: Flood Stream
listedValue.definition: The horizontal movement of water associated with the rising tide. Flood streams generally set towards the shore, or in the direction of the tide progression.

listedValue.label: Ebb Stream
listedValue.definition: The horizontal movement of water associated with falling tide. Ebb streams generally set seaward, or in the opposite direction to the tide progression.

listedValue.label: Other Tidal Flow
listedValue.definition: Any other horizontal movement of water associated with tides, for example rotary flow.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Category of Vegetation
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Classification of the plant life of an area or region.

listedValue.label: Bush
listedValue.definition: A shrub or clump of shrubs with stems of moderate length.

listedValue.label: Deciduous Wood
listedValue.definition: A wood with trees that shed their leaves annually.

listedValue.label: Coniferous Wood
listedValue.definition: A wood with evergreen trees of a group usually bearing cones, including yews, cedars and redwoods.

listedValue.label: Wood in General (inc Mixed Wood)
listedValue.definition: Growing trees densely occupying a tract of land.

listedValue.label: Mangroves
listedValue.definition: One of several genera of tropical trees or shrubs which produce many prop roots and grow along low-lying coasts into shallow water.

listedValue.label: Reed
listedValue.definition: [1] A reed uses compressed air and emits a weak, high pitched sound. [2] Any of various water or marsh plants with a firm stem. (Concise Oxford English Dictionary)

listedValue.label: Tree in General
listedValue.definition: An individual woody perennial plant, typically having a single stem or trunk growing to a considerable height and bearing lateral branches at some distance from the ground.

listedValue.label: Evergreen Tree
listedValue.definition: Having green foliage all the year round.

listedValue.label: Coniferous Tree
listedValue.definition: A cone-bearing, needle-leaved or scale-leaved evergreen tree.

listedValue.label: Palm Tree
listedValue.definition: A tropical or sub-tropical tree, shrub or vine having a tall, unbranched, columnar trunk. The trunk is crowned by a tuft or large, pleated fan or feather shaped leaves with stout sheathing and often prickly petioles (stalks), the persistent bases of which frequently clothe the trunk.

listedValue.label: Nipa Palm Tree
listedValue.definition: A rare palm tree with regular branching involving equal or sub-equal division of the apex that results in forking.

listedValue.label: Casuarina Tree
listedValue.definition: A tree characterized by slender, green, often drooping branches that are deeply grooved and that bear, at intervals, whorls of tine leaves.

listedValue.label: Eucalypt Tree
listedValue.definition: An instance of a large genus of mostly very large trees (90 metres).

listedValue.label: Deciduous Tree
listedValue.definition: Sheds its leaves each year at the end of the period of growth.

listedValue.label: Mangrove Tree
listedValue.definition: One of several genera of tropical trees or shrubs which produce many prop roots and grow along low-lying coasts into shallow water.

listedValue.label: Filao Tree
listedValue.definition: Casuarina equisetifolia, the most widespread and well-known member of the family Casuarinaceae.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Category of Water Turbulence
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Classification of an unstable sea state.

listedValue.label: Breakers
listedValue.definition: Waves breaking on the shore, over a reef, etc. Breakers may be roughly classified into three kinds, although the categories may overlap: spilling breakers break gradually over a considerable distance; plunging breakers tend to curl over and break with a crash; and surging breakers peak up, but then instead of spilling or plunging they surge up on the beach face. The French word 'brisant' is also used for the obstacle causing the breaking of the wave.

listedValue.label: Eddies
listedValue.definition: Circular movements of water usually formed where currents pass obstructions, between two adjacent currents flowing counter to each other, or along the edge of a permanent current.

listedValue.label: Overfalls
listedValue.definition: Short, breaking waves occurring when a strong current passes over a shoal or other submarine obstruction or meets a contrary current or wind.

listedValue.label: Tide Rips
listedValue.definition: Small waves formed on the surface of water by the meeting of opposing tidal currents or by a tidal current crossing an irregular bottom. Vertical oscillation, rather than progressive waves, is characteristic of tide rips.

listedValue.label: Bombora
listedValue.definition: A wave that forms over a submerged offshore reef or rock, sometimes (in very calm weather or at high tide) nearly swelling but in other conditions breaking heavily and producing a dangerous stretch of broken water; the reef or rock itself.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Category of Weed/Kelp
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Classification of marine vegetation of the algae class.

listedValue.label: Kelp
listedValue.definition: A giant plant sometimes 60 metres long with no roots, it is anchored by hold-fasts or tendrils up to 10 metres long, that cling to rock. Gas filled bubbles on fronds act as floats keeping the kelp just below the surface.

listedValue.label: Seaweed
listedValue.definition: The general name for marine plants of the Algae class which grow in long narrow ribbons.

listedValue.label: Sargasso
listedValue.definition: A certain type of sea weed, or more generally, a large floating mass of this sea weed.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Category of Wreck
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Classification of a wrecked or ruined ship.

listedValue.label: Non-Dangerous Wreck
listedValue.definition: A wreck which is not considered to be dangerous to surface navigation.

listedValue.label: Dangerous Wreck
listedValue.definition: A wreck submerged at such a depth as to be considered dangerous to surface navigation.

listedValue.label: Distributed Remains of Wreck
listedValue.definition: A substantively decayed wreck over which it is safe to navigate but which should be avoided for anchoring, taking the ground or ground fishing.

listedValue.label: Wreck Showing Mast/Masts
listedValue.definition: Wreck of which only the mast(s) is visible at the sounding datum indicated.

listedValue.label: Wreck Showing Any Portion of Hull or Superstructure
listedValue.definition: Wreck of which any portion of the hull or superstructure is visible at the sounding datum indicated.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Category of Zone of Confidence In Data
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Classification of the zone of confidence in data within an area based on the positional accuracy, survey equipment and coverage.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: See S-57 Appendix A, Chapter 2, Page 2.107 for the full list of ZOC categories.

listedValue.label: Zone of Confidence A1
listedValue.definition: Positional Accuracy +/- 5 metres; Depth Accuracy 0.5 metre +1% depth; Full area search undertaken. Significant seafloor features detected and depths measured; Controlled, systematic survey, high position and depth accuracy achieved using DGPS or a minimum three high quality lines of position (LOP) and a multibeam, channel or mechanical sweep system.

listedValue.label: Zone of Confidence A2
listedValue.definition: Positional Accuracy +/- 20 metres; Depth Accuracy 1.0 metre + 2% depth; Full area search undertaken. Significant seafloor features detected and depths measured; Controlled, systematic survey achieving position and depth accuracy less than ZOC A1 and using a modern survey echosounder and a sonar or mechanical sweep system.

listedValue.label: Zone of Confidence B
listedValue.definition: Positional Accuracy +/- 50 metres; Depth Accuracy 1.0 metre + 2% depth; Full area search not achieved, uncharted features hazardous to surface navigation are not expected but may exist; Controlled, systematic survey achieving similar depth but lesser position accuracies than ZOCA2, using a modern survey echosounder, but no sonar or mechanical sweep system.

listedValue.label: Zone of Confidence C
listedValue.definition: Positional Accuracy +/- 500 metres; Depth Accuracy 2.0 metre + 5% depth; Full area search not achieved, depth anomalies may be expected; Low accuracy survey or data collected on an opportunity basis such as soundings on passage.

listedValue.label: Zone of Confidence D
listedValue.definition: Positional Accuracy worse than ZOC C; Depth Accuracy worse than ZOC C; Full area search not achieved, large depth anomalies may be expected; Poor quality data or data that cannot be quality assessed due to lack of information.

listedValue.label: Zone of Confidence U
listedValue.definition: The quality of the bathymetric data has yet to be assessed.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Colour
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The property possessed by an object of producing different sensations on the eye as a result of the way it reflects or emits light.

listedValue.label: White
listedValue.definition: The achromatic object colour of greatest lightness characteristically perceived to belong to objects that reflect diffusely nearly all incident energy throughout the visible spectrum.

listedValue.label: Black
listedValue.definition: The achromatic color of least lightness characteristically perceived to belong to objects that neither reflect nor transmit light.

listedValue.label: Red
listedValue.definition: A color whose hue resembles that of blood or of the ruby or is that of the long-wave extreme of the visible spectrum.

listedValue.label: Green
listedValue.definition: Of the color green.

listedValue.label: Blue
listedValue.definition: A color whose hue is that of the clear sky or that of the portion of the color spectrum lying between green and violet.

listedValue.label: Yellow
listedValue.definition: A color whose hue resembles that of ripe lemons or sunflowers or is that of the portion of the spectrum lying between green and orange.

listedValue.label: Grey
listedValue.definition: Of the color grey.

listedValue.label: Brown
listedValue.definition: Any of a group of colors between red and yellow in hue, of medium to low lightness, and of moderate to low saturation.

listedValue.label: Amber
listedValue.definition: A variable color averaging a dark orange yellow.

listedValue.label: Violet
listedValue.definition: Any of a group of colors of reddish-blue hue, low lightness, and medium saturation.

listedValue.label: Orange
listedValue.definition: Any of a group of colors that are between red and yellow in hue.

listedValue.label: Magenta
listedValue.definition: A deep purplish red.

listedValue.label: Pink
listedValue.definition: Any of a group of colors bluish red to red in hue, of medium to high lightness, and of low to moderate saturation.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Colour Pattern
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A regular repeated design containing more than one colour.

listedValue.label: Horizontal Stripes
listedValue.definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented horizontally.

listedValue.label: Vertical Stripes
listedValue.definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented vertically.

listedValue.label: Diagonal Stripes
listedValue.definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented diagonally (that is, not horizontally or vertically).

listedValue.label: Squared
listedValue.definition: Often referred to as checker plate, where alternate colours are used to create squares similar to a chess or draught board. The pattern may be straight or diagonal.

listedValue.label: Stripes (Direction Unknown)
listedValue.definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented in an unknown direction.

listedValue.label: Border Stripe
listedValue.definition: A band or stripe of colour which is displayed around the outer edge of the object, which may also form a border to an inner pattern or plain colour.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Communication Channel
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A channel number assigned to a specific radio frequency, frequencies or frequency band.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: The expected input is the specific VHF-Channel. The attribute 'communication channel' encodes the various VHF-channels used for communication.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Condition
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The various conditions of buildings and other constructions.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: The default 'condition' should be considered to be completed, undamaged and working normally.

listedValue.label: Under Construction
listedValue.definition: Being built but not yet capable of function.

listedValue.label: Ruined
listedValue.definition: A structure in a decayed or deteriorated condition resulting from neglect or disuse, or a damaged structure in need of repair.

listedValue.label: Under Reclamation
listedValue.definition: An area of the sea, a lake or the navigable part of a river that is being reclaimed as land, usually by the dumping of earth and other material.

listedValue.label: Wingless
listedValue.definition: A windmill or wind turbine from which the vanes or turbine blades are missing.

listedValue.label: Planned Construction
listedValue.definition: Detailed planning has been completed but construction has not been initiated.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Contact Instructions
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Instructions provided on how to contact a particular person, organisation or service.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Data Assessment
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The categorization of the assessment level of bathymetric data for an area.

listedValue.label: Assessed
listedValue.definition: The quality of the bathymetric data has been assessed.

listedValue.label: Assessed (Oceanic)
listedValue.definition: The quality of oceanic bathymetric data (depths deeper than 200 metres) has been assessed, however details are not required.

listedValue.label: Unassessed
listedValue.definition: Not having been assessed.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Date Disused
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The date that an entity ceases to be used.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Date End
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The latest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: The Date End should be encoded using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY), 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, indication of the month and/or day is omitted, and replaced with dashes (-). When no specific year is required (that is, the event or date range ends at the same time each year) the following two cases may be considered:- same day each year: ----MMDD- same month each year: ----MM--This conforms to ISO 8601: 2004. Date End indicates the latest date of an event or the end of a date range. It is used to indicate the end of a fixed date range, the end of a periodic date range, or the removal or cancellation of a feature at a specific date in the future.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Date Fixed
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The date of an event.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Date Start
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The earliest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: The Date Start should be encoded using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY), 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, indication of the month and/or day is omitted, and replaced with dashes (-). When no specific year is required (that is, the event or date range ends at the same time each year) the following two cases may be considered:- same day each year: ----MMDD- same month each year: ----MM--This conforms to ISO 8601: 2004. Date Start indicates the earliest date of an event or the start of a date range. It is used to indicate the start of a fixed date range, the start of a periodic date range, or the deployment or implementation of a feature at a specific date in the future.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Date Variable
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A day which is not fixed in the Gregorian calendar.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: Examples: The fourth Thursday in November; new moon day of Kartika (Diwali); Easter Sunday.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Day of Week
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Any one of seven days in a week.

listedValue.label: Sunday
listedValue.definition: The first day of the week.

listedValue.label: Monday
listedValue.definition: The second day of the week.

listedValue.label: Tuesday
listedValue.definition: The third day of the week.

listedValue.label: Wednesday
listedValue.definition: The fourth day of the week.

listedValue.label: Thursday
listedValue.definition: The fifth day of the week.

listedValue.label: Friday
listedValue.definition: The sixth day of the week.

listedValue.label: Saturday
listedValue.definition: The seventh day of the week.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Day of Week is Range
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A statement expressing if the days of the week identified define a range or not.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: A True value is an indication that the identified days of the week define a range between and inclusive of those days.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Default Clearance Depth
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The depth value determined for an underwater hazard of unknown depth, based on the depth of the surrounding area.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Depth Range Maximum Value
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The maximum (deepest) value of a depth range.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: Where the area dries, the value is negative.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Depth Range Minimum Value
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The minimum (shoalest) value of a depth range.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: Where the area dries, the value is negative.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Destination
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The place or general direction to which a vessel is going or directed.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: In addition to a place name of a port, harbour area or terminal, the place could include generalities such as The north-west, or upriver.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Display Name
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A statement expressing if a feature name is to be displayed in certain system display settings or not.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: Where it is allowable to encode multiple instances of feature name for a single feature instance, only one feature name instance can indicate that the name is to be displayed (display name set to True).

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Display Uncertainties
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A statement defining whether an encoded feature is to have its horizontal position and vertical accuracies displayed or not.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Distance Unit of Measurement
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A specified amount of a quantity, as of length, by comparison with which any other quantity of the same kind is measured or estimated.

listedValue.label: Metres
listedValue.definition: The basic unit of length in the International System of Units (SI) system.

listedValue.label: Yards
listedValue.definition: A common unit of linear measure in English-speaking countries, equal to 3 feet or 36 inches, and equivalent to 0.9144 metre.

listedValue.label: Kilometres
listedValue.definition: A unit of length, the common measure of distances equal to 1000 metres, and equivalent to 3280.8 feet or 0.621 mile.

listedValue.label: Statute Miles
listedValue.definition: A unit equal to 5280 feet.

listedValue.label: Nautical Miles
listedValue.definition: A unit of length equal to 1,852 metres. This value was approved by the International Hydrographic Conference of 1929 and has been adopted by nearly all maritime states.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Dredged Date
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The date that dredging occurred.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: Dredged date indicates the latest date of dredging (which may be the latest known date if the dredged area is not maintained), or the date of the latest control survey confirming the depth in a maintained dredged area.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Elevation
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The altitude of the ground level of an object, measured from a specified vertical datum.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Estimated Range of Transmission
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The estimated range of a non-optical electromagnetic transmission.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: The estimated range (distance) assumes 'in vacuo' transmission and a standard antenna height of 5 metres. Thus it gives a hint to the mariner whether they are likely to receive transmission at a certain distance from an object.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Exhibition Condition of Light
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The outward display of the light.

listedValue.label: Light Shown Without Change of Character
listedValue.definition: A light shown throughout the 24 hours without change of character.

listedValue.label: Daytime Light
listedValue.definition: A light which is only exhibited by day.

listedValue.label: Fog Light
listedValue.definition: A light which is exhibited in fog or conditions of reduced visibility.

listedValue.label: Night Light
listedValue.definition: A light which is only exhibited at night.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Exposition of Sounding
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Indicates the relationship of the depth of a feature to the range of depth of the surrounding depth area.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: These objects could be a potential danger for navigation.

listedValue.label: Within the Range of Depth of the Surrounding Depth Area
listedValue.definition: The depth corresponds to the depth range of the surrounding depth area; that is, the depth is not shoaler than the minimum depth of the surrounding depth area or deeper than the maximum depth of the surrounding depth area.

listedValue.label: Shoaler Than the Range of Depth of the Surrounding Depth Area
listedValue.definition: The depth is shoaler than the minimum depth of the surrounding depth area.

listedValue.label: Deeper Than the Range of Depth of the Surrounding Depth Area
listedValue.definition: The depth is deeper than the maximum depth of the surrounding depth area.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: File Locator
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The location of a fragment of text or other information in a support file.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: Application schemas must describe how the associated file is identified. The associated file will commonly be named in a file reference co-attribute of the same complex attribute. Each DCEG must specify requirements for the format of the associated file and the semantics of file locator. For example, the value of file locator may be an HTML ID in an HTML file, line number in a text file) or a bookmark in a PDF file.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: File Reference
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The file name of an externally referenced text file.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Flare Angle
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The angle about which the light flare symbol is rotated to be displayed in ECDIS.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: The flare angle is calculated by ENC production software systems.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Flare Stack
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A tall structure used for burning-off waste oil or gas.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Flip Bearing
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The bearing at which text is re-located to the opposite side of a feature when screen display is oriented away from true north.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Frequency Shore Station Receives
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The shore station receiver frequency.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: Examples: 4379.1 kHz becomes 043791; 13162.8 kHz becomes 131628.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Frequency Shore Station Transmits
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The shore station transmitter frequency.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: Examples: 4379.1 kHz becomes 043791; 13162.8 kHz becomes 131628.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Full Seafloor Coverage Achieved
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Expression stating if full seafloor coverage has been achieved in the area covered by hydrographic surveys.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: Full seafloor coverage achieved applies to both the spatial completeness of feature detection and to the spatial completeness of the measurement of the regular seafloor. The former is further specified by the complex attribute features detected, the latter by the attributes depth range maximum value and depth range minimum value.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Function
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A specific role that describes a feature.

listedValue.label: Harbour-Masters Office
listedValue.definition: A local official who has charge of mooring and berthing of vessels, collecting harbour fees, etc.

listedValue.label: Customs Office
listedValue.definition: Serves as a government office where customs duties are collected, the flow of goods are regulated and restrictions enforced, and shipments or vehicles are cleared for entering or leaving a country.

listedValue.label: Health Office
listedValue.definition: The office which is charged with the administration of health laws and sanitary inspections.

listedValue.label: Hospital
listedValue.definition: An institution or establishment providing medical or surgical treatment for the ill or wounded.

listedValue.label: Post Office
listedValue.definition: The public department, agency or organisation responsible primarily for the collection, transmission and distribution of mail.

listedValue.label: Hotel
listedValue.definition: An establishment, especially of a comfortable or luxurious kind, where paying visitors are provided with accommodation, meals and other services.

listedValue.label: Railway Station
listedValue.definition: A building with platforms where trains arrive, load, discharge and depart.

listedValue.label: Police Station
listedValue.definition: The headquarters of a local police force and that is where those under arrest are first charged.

listedValue.label: Water-Police Station
listedValue.definition: The headquarters of a local water-police force.

listedValue.label: Pilot Office
listedValue.definition: The office or headquarters of pilots; the place where the services of a pilot may be obtained.

listedValue.label: Pilot Lookout
listedValue.definition: A distinctive structure or place on shore from which personnel keep watch upon events at sea or along the coast.

listedValue.label: Bank Office
listedValue.definition: An office for custody, deposit, loan, exchange or issue of money.

listedValue.label: Headquarters for District Control
listedValue.definition: The quarters of an executive officer (director, manager, etc.) with responsibility for an administrative area.

listedValue.label: Transit Shed/Warehouse
listedValue.definition: A building or part of a building for storage of wares or goods.

listedValue.label: Factory
listedValue.definition: A building or buildings with equipment for manufacturing; a workshop.

listedValue.label: Power Station
listedValue.definition: A stationary plant containing apparatus for large scale conversion of some form of energy (such as hydraulic, steam, chemical or nuclear energy) into electrical energy.

listedValue.label: Administrative
listedValue.definition: A building for the management of affairs.

listedValue.label: Educational Facility
listedValue.definition: A building concerned with education (for example school, college, university, etc).

listedValue.label: Church
listedValue.definition: A building for public Christian worship.

listedValue.label: Chapel
listedValue.definition: A place for Christian worship other than a parish, cathedral or church, especially one attached to a private house or institution.

listedValue.label: Temple
listedValue.definition: A building for public Jewish worship.

listedValue.label: Pagoda
listedValue.definition: A Hindu or Buddhist temple or sacred building.

listedValue.label: Shinto Shrine
listedValue.definition: A building for public Shinto worship.

listedValue.label: Buddhist Temple
listedValue.definition: A building for public Buddhist worship.

listedValue.label: Mosque
listedValue.definition: A Muslim place of worship.

listedValue.label: Marabout
listedValue.definition: A shrine marking the burial place of a Muslim holy man.

listedValue.label: Lookout
listedValue.definition: Keeping a watch upon events at sea or along the coast.

listedValue.label: Communication
listedValue.definition: Transmitting and/or receiving electronic communication signals.

listedValue.label: Television
listedValue.definition: A system for reproducing on a screen visual images transmitted (usually with sound) by radio signals.

listedValue.label: Radio
listedValue.definition: Transmitting and/or receiving radio-frequency electromagnetic waves as a means of communication.

listedValue.label: Radar
listedValue.definition: A method, system or technique of using beamed, reflected, and timed radio waves for detecting, locating, or tracking objects, and for measuring altitudes.

listedValue.label: Light Support
listedValue.definition: A structure serving as a support for one or more lights.

listedValue.label: Microwave
listedValue.definition: Broadcasting and receiving signals using microwaves.

listedValue.label: Cooling
listedValue.definition: Generation of chilled liquid and/or gas for cooling purposes.

listedValue.label: Observation
listedValue.definition: A place from which the surroundings can be observed but at which a watch is not habitually maintained.

listedValue.label: Timeball
listedValue.definition: A visual time signal in the form of a ball.

listedValue.label: Clock
listedValue.definition: Instrument for measuring time and recording hours.

listedValue.label: Control
listedValue.definition: Used to control the flow of traffic within a specified range of an installation.

listedValue.label: Airship Mooring
listedValue.definition: Equipment or structure to secure an airship.

listedValue.label: Stadium
listedValue.definition: An arena for holding and viewing events.

listedValue.label: Bus Station
listedValue.definition: A building where buses and coaches regularly stop to take on and/or let off passengers, especially for long-distance travel.

listedValue.label: Sea Rescue Control
listedValue.definition: A unit responsible for promoting efficient organization of search and rescue services and for coordinating the conduct of search and rescue operations within a search and rescue region.

listedValue.label: Observatory
listedValue.definition: A building designed and equipped for making observations of astronomical, meteorological, or other natural phenomena.

listedValue.label: Ore Crusher
listedValue.definition: A building or structure used to crush ore.

listedValue.label: Boathouse
listedValue.definition: A building or shed, usually built partly over water, for sheltering a boat or boats.

listedValue.label: Pumping Station
listedValue.definition: A facility to move solids, liquids or gases by means of pressure or suction.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Headline
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Words set at the head of a passage or page to introduce or categorize.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Height
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The value of the vertical distance to the highest point of the object, measured from a specified vertical datum.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: Height must not be used for floating objects.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Horizontal Clearance Length
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The length of a feature, such as a lock or basin, which is available for safe navigation. This may, or may not, be the same as the total physical length of the feature.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Horizontal Clearance Value
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The width of an object, such as a canal or a tunnel, which is available for safe navigation. This may, or may not, be the same as the total physical width of the object.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Horizontal Clearance Width
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The width of an object, such as a lock or basin, which is available for safe navigation. This may, or may not, be the same as the total physical width of the object.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Horizontal Distance Uncertainty
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The best estimate of the horizontal accuracy of horizontal clearances and distances.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: The error is assumed to be positive and negative. The plus/minus character must not be encoded.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Horizontal Length
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A measurement of the longer of two linear axis.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Horizontal Width
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A measurement of the shorter of two linear axis.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Ice Factor
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The value of the maximum variation in the vertical clearance of an overhead cable due to an accumulation of ice.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: IMO Adopted
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A defined maritime traffic route that has been adopted as an IMO routeing measure.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: In Dispute
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A statement that expresses if an area is in a jurisdictional dispute.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: In the Water
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: An indication if the feature is located in or over navigable water.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: A True value is an indication that the feature is to be included in the ECDIS Base Display viewing group.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Is MRCC
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A statement that expresses if a coastguard station performs the function of a Maritime Rescue and Coordination Centre.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: A True value is an indication that an encoded coastguard station performs the function of a Maritime Rescue and Coordination Centre.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Jurisdiction
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The jurisdiction applicable to an administrative area.

listedValue.label: International
listedValue.definition: Involving more than one country; covering more than one national area.

listedValue.label: National
listedValue.definition: An area administered or controlled by a single nation.

listedValue.label: National Sub-Division
listedValue.definition: An area smaller than the nation in which it lies.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Language
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The method of human communication, either spoken or written, consisting of the use of words in a structured and conventional way.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: The language is encoded by a 3 character code following ISO 639-2/T.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Least Depth of Detected Features Measured
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Expression stating if the least depth of detected features in an area was measured.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: A feature in this context is any object, whether man-made or not, projecting above the sea floor, which may be a danger for surface navigation (reference: IHO publication S-44).- least depth of detected features measured does not describe the least depth of features that were actually detected during a hydrographic survey, but the ability of the survey to detect the least depth of features with a maximum uncertainty as defined in IHO publication S-44.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Lifting Capacity
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The specific safe lifting capacity of a feature.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Light Characteristic
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The distinct character, such as fixed, flashing, or occulting, which is given to each light to avoid confusion with neighbouring ones.

listedValue.label: Fixed
listedValue.definition: A signal light that shows continuously, in any given direction, with constant luminous intensity and colour.

listedValue.label: Flashing
listedValue.definition: A rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly shorter than the total duration of darkness and all the appearances of light are of equal duration.

listedValue.label: Long-Flashing
listedValue.definition: A single-flashing light in which a single flash of not less than two seconds duration is regularly repeated.

listedValue.label: Quick-Flashing
listedValue.definition: A rhythmic light in which flashes are repeated at a rate of not less than 50 flashes per minutes but less than 80 flashes per minutes. It may be: - Continuous quick-flashing: A quick-flashing light in which a flash is regularly repeated. - Group quick-flashing: A quick-flashing light in which a group of two or more flashes, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

listedValue.label: Very Quick-Flashing
listedValue.definition: A rhythmic light in which flashes are repeated at a rate of not less than 80 flashes per minute but less than 160 flashes per minute. It may be:- Continuous very quick-flashing: A very quick-flashing light in which a flash is regularly repeated.- Group very quick-flashing: A very quick-flashing light in which a group of two or more flashes, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

listedValue.label: Continuous Ultra Quick-Flashing
listedValue.definition: A rhythmic light in which flashes are regularly repeated at a rate of not less than 160 flashes per minute.

listedValue.label: Isophased
listedValue.definition: A light with all durations of light and darkness equal.

listedValue.label: Occulting
listedValue.definition: A rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly longer than the total duration of darkness and all the eclipses are of equal duration. It may be: - Single-occulting: An occulting light in which an eclipse is regularly repeated. - Group-occulting: An occulting light in which a group of two or more eclipses, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated. - Composite group-occulting: An occulting light in which a sequence of groups of one or more eclipses, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated, and the groups comprise different numbers of eclipses.

listedValue.label: Interrupted Ultra Quick-Flashing
listedValue.definition: A light in which the ultra quick flashes (160 or more per minute) are interrupted at regular intervals by eclipses of long duration.

listedValue.label: Morse
listedValue.definition: A rhythmic light in which appearances of light of two clearly different durations are grouped to represent a character or characters in the Morse code.

listedValue.label: Fixed and Flash
listedValue.definition: A rhythmic light in which a fixed light is combined with a flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

listedValue.label: Flash and Long-Flash
listedValue.definition: A rhythmic light in which a flashing light is combined with a long-flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

listedValue.label: Occulting and Flash
listedValue.definition: A rhythmic light in which an occulting light is combined with a flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

listedValue.label: Fixed and Long-Flash
listedValue.definition: A rhythmic light in which a fixed light is combined with a long-flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

listedValue.label: Occulting Alternating
listedValue.definition: An alternating light in which the total duration of light in each period is clearly longer than the total duration of darkness and in which the intervals of darkness (occultations) are all of equal duration.

listedValue.label: Long-Flash Alternating
listedValue.definition: An alternating single-flashing light in which an appearance of light of not less than two seconds duration is regularly repeated.

listedValue.label: Flash Alternating
listedValue.definition: An alternating rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly shorter than the total duration of darkness and all the appearances of light are of equal duration.

listedValue.label: Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
listedValue.definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

listedValue.label: Very Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
listedValue.definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of very quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

listedValue.label: Ultra Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
listedValue.definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of ultra quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

listedValue.label: Alternating
listedValue.definition: A signal light that shows, in any given direction, two or more colours in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

listedValue.label: Fixed and Alternating Flashing
listedValue.definition: A rhythmic light in which a fixed light is combined with a flashing light of higher luminous intensity and different colour.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Light Visibility
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The specific visibility of a light, with respect to the light's intensity and ease of recognition.

listedValue.label: High Intensity
listedValue.definition: Non-marine lights with a higher power than marine lights and visible from well off shore (often 'Aero' lights).

listedValue.label: Low Intensity
listedValue.definition: Non-marine lights with lower power than marine lights.

listedValue.label: Faint
listedValue.definition: A decrease in the apparent intensity of a light which may occur in the case of partial obstructions.

listedValue.label: Intensified
listedValue.definition: A light in a sector is intensified (that is, has longer range than other sectors).

listedValue.label: Unintensified
listedValue.definition: A light in a sector is unintensified (that is, has shorter range than other sectors).

listedValue.label: Visibility Deliberately Restricted
listedValue.definition: A light sector is deliberately reduced in intensity, for example to reduce its effect on a built-up area.

listedValue.label: Obscured
listedValue.definition: Said of the arc of a light sector designated by its limiting bearings in which the light is not visible from seaward.

listedValue.label: Partially Obscured
listedValue.definition: This value specifies that parts of the sector are obscured.

listedValue.label: Visible in Line of Range
listedValue.definition: Lights that must in line to be visible.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Line Spacing Maximum
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The maximum distance between hydrographic survey lines.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Line Spacing Minimum
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The minimum distance between hydrographic survey lines.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Linkage
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Location (address) for on-line access using a URL/URI address or similar addressing scheme.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Magnetic Anomaly Value Maximum
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The maximum value of the deviation from the normal magnetic variation.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: The deviation is assumed to be positive and negative. The plus/minus character must not be encoded.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Magnetic Anomaly Value Minimum
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Negative value of the deviation from the normal magnetic variation.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: The deviation is assumed to be negative.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Major Light
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A statement expressing if a light is considered to be a major light in terms of ECDIS display in a particular area.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: Major light is only intended to provide an indication to the ECDIS that the light is considered to be an important light in terms of its display. As such this is a cartographic attribute to aid the compiler in determining the most appropriate display for a light; it is not intended to be used as a formal classification method for lights.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Marks Navigational - System Of
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The system of navigational buoyage a region complies with.

listedValue.label: IALA A
listedValue.definition: Navigational aids conform to the International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA A system.

listedValue.label: IALA B
listedValue.definition: Navigational aids conform to the International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA B system.

listedValue.label: No System
listedValue.definition: Navigational aids do not conform to any defined system.

listedValue.label: CEVNI
listedValue.definition: CEVNI (European Code for Navigation on Inland Waterways) is the European code for rivers, canals land lakes in most of Europe.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Maximum Display Scale
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The largest intended viewing scale for the data.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Maximum Permitted Draught
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The maximum draught of a vessel permitted along a route, in a channel or dock, at a berth, or over a submerged feature.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Measured Distance
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A course at sea, whose ends are indicated by ranges ashore, and whose length has been accurately measured for determining the speed of vessels.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Measurement Distance Maximum
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The maximum spacing of the principal measurement lines of a hydrographic survey.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Measurement Distance Minimum
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The minimum spacing of the principal measurement lines of a hydrographic survey.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Minimum Display Scale
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The smallest intended viewing scale for the data.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: MMSI Code
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The Maritime Mobile Service Identity (MMSI) Code is formed of a series of nine digits which are transmitted over the radio path in order to uniquely identify ship stations, ship earth stations,coast stations, coast earth stations, and group calls. These identities are formed in such a way that the identity or part thereof can be used by telephone and telex subscribers connected to the general telecommunications network principally to call ships automatically.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Moire Effect
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: A short range (up to 2km) type of directional light. Sodium lighting gives a yellow background to a screen on which a vertical black line will be seen by an observer on the centre line.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Multiplicity Known
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The number of features of identical character that exist as a co-located group is or is not known.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Name
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The individual name of a feature.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Name of Resource
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Name of the online resource.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Nationality
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Identifier of membership of a particular nation.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Nature of Construction
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The building's primary construction material.

listedValue.label: Masonry
listedValue.definition: Constructed of stones or bricks, usually quarried, shaped, and mortared.

listedValue.label: Concreted
listedValue.definition: Constructed of concrete, a material made of sand and gravel that is united by cement into a hardened mass used for roads, foundations, etc.

listedValue.label: Loose Boulders
listedValue.definition: Constructed from large stones or blocks of concrete, often placed loosely for protection against waves or water turbulence.

listedValue.label: Hard Surfaced
listedValue.definition: Constructed with a surface of hard material, usually a term applied to roads surfaced with asphalt or concrete.

listedValue.label: Unsurfaced
listedValue.definition: Constructed with no extra protection, usually a term applied to roads not surfaced with a hard material.

listedValue.label: Wooden
listedValue.definition: Constructed from wood.

listedValue.label: Metal
listedValue.definition: Constructed from metal.

listedValue.label: Glass Reinforced Plastic
listedValue.definition: Constructed from a plastic material strengthened with fibres of glass.

listedValue.label: Latticed
listedValue.definition: A structure of crossed wooden or metal strips usually arranged to form a diagonal pattern of open spaces between the strips.

listedValue.label: Glass
listedValue.definition: [1] Any artificial or natural substance having similar properties and composition, as fused borax, obsidian, or the like. [2] Something made of such a substance, as a windowpane.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Nature of Surface
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The general material which the land surface or the sea bed is composed.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: Mud, sand, stone, rock are terms used for the general description. Clay, silt, gravel, pebbles, cobbles are more specific terms related to particle size.

listedValue.label: Mud
listedValue.definition: Soft, wet earth.

listedValue.label: Clay
listedValue.definition: (Particles of less than 0.002mm); stiff, sticky earth that becomes hard when baked.

listedValue.label: Silt
listedValue.definition: An unconsolidated sediment whose particles range in size from 00039 to 00625 millimetres in diameter (between clay and sand size).

listedValue.label: Sand
listedValue.definition: Loose material consisting of small but easily distinguishable, separate grains, between 0.0625 and 2.000 millimetres in diameter.

listedValue.label: Stone
listedValue.definition: A general term for rock and rock fragments ranging in size from pebbles and gravel to boulders or large rock masses.

listedValue.label: Gravel
listedValue.definition: (Particles of 2.0 - 4.0mm); small stones with coarse sand.

listedValue.label: Pebbles
listedValue.definition: A small stone worn smooth and rounded by the action of water, sand, ice, etc. ranging in diameter between 4 and 64 millimetres.

listedValue.label: Cobbles
listedValue.definition: A naturally rounded stone larger than a pebble.

listedValue.label: Rock
listedValue.definition: Any formation of natural origin that constitutes an integral part of the lithosphere. The natural occurring material that forms firm, hard, and solid masses.

listedValue.label: Lava
listedValue.definition: The fluid or semi-fluid matter flowing from a volcano. The substance that results from the cooling of the molten rock. Part of the ocean bed is composed of lava.

listedValue.label: Coral
listedValue.definition: Hard calcareous skeletons of many tribes of marine polyps.

listedValue.label: Shells
listedValue.definition: The hard outside covering of an animal. Part of the ocean bed is composed of numerous shells of marine animals.

listedValue.label: Boulder
listedValue.definition: A rounded rock with diameter of 256 millimetres or larger.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Nature of Surface - Qualifying Terms
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The nature of various forms of natural surface materials in terms of their size, morphology and consistency.

listedValue.label: Fine
listedValue.definition: Falls within the smallest size continuum for a particular nature of surface term.

listedValue.label: Medium
listedValue.definition: Falls within the moderate size continuum for a particular nature of surface term.

listedValue.label: Coarse
listedValue.definition: Falls within the largest size continuum for a particular nature of surface term.

listedValue.label: Broken
listedValue.definition: Fractured or in pieces.

listedValue.label: Sticky
listedValue.definition: Having an adhesive or glue like property.

listedValue.label: Soft
listedValue.definition: Not hard or firm.

listedValue.label: Stiff
listedValue.definition: Not pliant; thick, resistant to flow.

listedValue.label: Volcanic
listedValue.definition: Composed of or containing material ejected from a volcano.

listedValue.label: Calcareous
listedValue.definition: Composed of or containing calcium or calcium carbonate.

listedValue.label: Hard
listedValue.definition: Firm; usually refers to an area of the sea floor not covered by unconsolidated sediment.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Number of Features
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The number of features of identical character that exist as a co-located group.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Orientation Uncertainty
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The best estimate of the accuracy of a bearing.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Orientation Value
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The angular distance measured from true north to the major axis of the feature.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Pictorial Representation
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Indicates whether a pictorial representation of the feature is available.
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.remarks: The 'pictorial representation' could be a drawing or a photo. The string encodes the file name of an external graphic file (pixel/vector).

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Pilot Movement
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: Classification of pilot activity by arrival, departure, or change of pilot. It may also describe the place where the pilot's advice begins, ends, or is transferred to a different pilot.

listedValue.label: Embarkation
listedValue.definition: The place where vessels not being navigated according to a pilots instructions pick up a pilot while in transit from sea to a port or constricted waters for future navigation under pilot instructions.

listedValue.label: Disembarkation
listedValue.definition: The place where vessels being navigated under a pilots instructions in transit from sea to a port or constricted waters drop the pilot and proceed without being subject to pilot instructions.

listedValue.label: Pilot Change
listedValue.definition: The place where vessels being navigated under a pilots instructions drop off the pilot and pick up a different pilot for future navigation under pilots instructions.

S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.name: Product
S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.definition: The various substances which are transported, stored or exploited.

listedValue.label: Oil
listedValue.definition: A thick, slippery liquid that will not dissolve in water, usually petroleum based in the context of storage tanks.

listedValue.label: Gas
listedValue.definition: A substance with particles that can move freely, usually a fuel substance in the context of storage tanks.

listedValue.label: Water
listedValue.definition: A colourless, odourless, tasteless liquid that is a compound of hydrogen and oxygen.

listedValue.label: Stone
